						<summary>

						<p>Slab (third, reverse) set up in front of the Vishṇu temple on the river bank.</p>						

						<p>The date portion is badly damaged. However, on the basis of palaeography this inscription may be assigned to the 16th century A.D.,</p>						

						<p>It seems to refer the consecration of the image of Chenna-kēśava and gifts made for its worship, offerings etc. It also mentions the village Guṟṟaṁpāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
